### PR summary [580b3f8f53](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16154/commits/580b3f8f530ed770a83229b8a89eee82e9d03aa8)

#### Import changes for modified files

No significant changes to the import graph


<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>

|Files|Import difference|
|-|-|

</details>

---

#### Declarations diff

No declarations were harmed in the making of this PR! üêô
<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>

## more verbose report:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>
```
</details>

The doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.

I took a look again: the changes to `Ring/Basic.lean` are not pretty, but I can certainly live with them (in exchange for not switching style half-way throughout the file).

I am not convinced by the readability regression in ToExpr. I tend to leave this alone, and perhaps add a comment instead.
Similarly, for Control/Random, my personal preferences is to have a comment instead.

I can mention this on zulip again (in a week or two; I have very little Lean time right now). I would maintainer merge the changes to Ring/Basic right away.

Build failed (retrying...):
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/10943821820/job/30384214490)

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/10945825181/job/30390917704)
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/10945825181/job/30390917373)

Thanks :tada:

bors merge

Thanks for looking into this! Quite a few of these changes seem positive to me. For example, I like how the Data/Vector changes turned out, they feel much cleaner than #14885.
- I'm on the fence about some files (say: Cache, the archive or deprecated files don't feel as important - one could also leave them alone). That said, the archive and cache changes are quite neutral/a net negative in lines of code, so I can certainly live with them.
- Control/Random in fact uses autoImplicit pervasively: I am not sure if changing this file is a net positive. (The most confusing feature of autoImplicit is if *some* declarations use it, but not all. When you change 5 out of 100 declarations, the consistency feels like a clear improvement. As the entire file seems to use it, I'm less convinced. Adding a comment that this is on purpose would also work.)
- Can you split Equiv/Basic into a separate PR, as that file is simply large enough?
- I am not convinced about the changes to `ToExpr`.

Thanks :tada:

bors merge
Why this change? This does not *seem* required.
`RandT m Œ±` depends on `StateT m Œ±`, the latter of which requires that the first universe in `{m : Type u ‚Üí Type*}` match the universe of `Œ±`.
Can somebody double-check this change is sane, please?
Why do you need this change?
It doesn't work the other way.

Please pull this change out into a separate PR. It seems unrelated?

But yes, it seems to be correct, and the universe ordering on `univLE_max` was "backwards" previously.
@semorrison #16690
Can you drop the quotes, and use `Q($Œ±)`, etc. instead?
Same in the other locations in this file.
In fact: can you move some of these implicit arguments into variables, say `u` and perhaps \alpha? (The others might clash with variables further below; it would be good to check those.)

It doesn't work. When I make `variable {u : Lean.Level} {Œ± : Q(Type u)}` I get the error
```
application type mismatch
  ExProd.eq ?m.8597 b‚ÇÇ
argument
  b‚ÇÇ
has type
  @ExProd Lean.Level.zero (Expr.const `Nat []) s‚Ñï e‚úù : Type
but is expected to have type
  @ExProd u Œ± s‚Ñï e‚úù : Type
```
Hm. I'm not sure about the changes in this file: the new version is *much* longer and feels less readable.

Actually it's quite logical. For the first three instances I copied code over from core and made it universe-polymorphic. The fourth explicitly written out instance follows the style of the first three.
Can you use Type* here, and/or move \alpha outside of the namespace?

pullRequest.title: [Merged by Bors] - chore: remove `autoImplicit` in `Tactic.Ring.Basic`
